We first calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio by determining the total liabilities and dividing by total assets. In the balance sheet, the only liabilities provided are under “Total Current Liabilities” which amount to 7,605,149.91. The “Total Assets” are 23,717,525.01. Thus,

 Debt to Asset Ratio = 7,605,149.91 / 23,717,525.01 ≈ 0.3205  
 Rounded to two decimals, this ratio is 0.32.

Next, we calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio using the cash flow statement and the income statement. The “Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities” is –967,147.02, while the “Net Profit” is 112,375.10. Thus,

 Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = –967,147.02 / 112,375.10 ≈ –8.61.
